sources.description:
Jane Eyre is an orphan, sent to Lowood school, and eventually becomes a governess at Thornfield hall to a girl named Adele. While she is there, many strange things happen and eventually she and Edward Rochester, owner of Thornfield and Adele's guardian, fall in love.

Director: Delbert Mann
Writers: Charlotte Brontë (novel), Jack Pulman
Stars: George C. Scott, Susannah York, Ian Bannen
Genre: Literary classics, Drama
